{"title_page": "Gushcloud International", "text_new": "{{short description|Global influencer and talent acquisition company.}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Gushcloud International\n| logo = Gushcloud International Logo.png\n| type = Talent agency\n| industry = \n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = 2011, [[Singapore]]\n| founder = Althea Lim, Vincent Ha\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = Singapore\n| area_served = Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines, Korea, Vietnam, Japan, China, and USA.\n| key_people = \n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = 300<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://cnaluxury.channelnewsasia.com/people/gushcloud-founders-althea-lim-vincent-ha-12064202|title=From crises to conquest: How Gushcloud's founders turned their business around|website=CNA Luxury|access-date=2019-11-13}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year = 2019<ref name=\":4\" />\n| parent = \n| website = https://gushcloud.com\n}}\n\n'''Gushcloud International''' is a global influencer, entertainment, and talent acquisition company. It is headquartered in [[Singapore]] and began in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-3m-yg-investment|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== History ==\nAlthea Lim and Vincent Ha are the co-founders of Gushcloud International,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-acquires-marketing-agency-dstnct/|title=Gushcloud acquires marketing agency DSTNCT|last=Farveen|first=Farzanah|date=2019-02-14|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> which has offices in Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines, Vietnam, South Korea, Japan, and the US, and 300+ employees.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-splits-from-yello-digital-founders-buy-back-company-for-us8-2m/|title=Gushcloud splits from Yello Digital, founders buy back company for US$8.2m|last=Tan|first=Janice|date=2018-11-16|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.femina.co.id/Career/belajar-menjadi-influencer-sukses-di-media-sosial|title=Belajar Menjadi Influencer Sukses di Media Sosial|last=Indonesia|first=Femina|date=2018-04-22|website=femina.co.id|language=id|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> Gushcloud International works with influencers, content creators, and celebrities in Asia. The establishment has five working units: marketing, talent, investment, entertainment, and technology.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nIn 2014, a blogger from Singapore, [[Xiaxue]], alleged that Gushcloud had unethical practices,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://says.com/my/news/everyone-is-talking-about-xiaxue-s-big-expose-on-gushcloud-can-i-have-a-summary-please|title=Everyone Is Talking About Xiaxue's Big Expos\u00e9 On Gushcloud. Can I Have A Summary Please?|last=Chu|first=Mei Mei|date=2014-12-24|website=SAYS|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> to which Gushcloud issued a point-by-point rebuttal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/singapore-startup-gushcloud-responds-xiaxues-accusations-lack-ethics|title=Singapore startup Gushcloud rebuts Xiaxue\u2019s accusations|last=Lee|first=Terence|date=23 December 2014|website=www.techinasia.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2015, Xiaxue once again alleged that [[Singtel#Gushcloud marketing scandal|Gushcloud had paid celebrity bloggers]] to write negatively against the rivals of [[Singtel]], which Singtel and Gushcloud initially denied but later apologised.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-weathered-a-pr-disaster-its-now-growing-and-profitable|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mumbrella.asia/2015/03/gushcloud-exposed-for-paying-celebrity-bloggers-to-write-negatively-about-singtel-competitors-singtel-denies-issuing-brief|title=Xiaxue exposes Gushcloud for paying celebrity bloggers to write negatively about Singtel rivals, Singtel denies issuing brief|last=Hicks|first=Robin|date=2015-03-17|website=Mumbrella Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tnp.sg/news/singtel-apologises-smear-campaign-against-rivals|title=Singtel apologises for smear campaign against rivals|last=Dhanaraj|first=Jennifer|date=2015-03-18|website=The New Paper|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Yello Digital Marketing Global (YDMG), based in [[South Korea]], gained control of the company by buying 62% shares for USD 7.5 million<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-weathered-a-pr-disaster-its-now-growing-and-profitable|title=Gushcloud weathered a PR disaster. It\u2019s now growing and profitable.|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/singapores-gushcloud-acquired-win-company|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> but in November 2018, the co-founders bought back the 62% shareholding from investor YDMG for USD 8.2 million.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-launches-new-sports-marketing-division/|title=Gushcloud launches new sports marketing division|date=2017-05-11|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> Between 2015 - 2018, it grew from three to nine markets.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nRussell Simmons, the co-founder of [[Def Jam Recordings]], became the President in September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/consumer/gushcloud-names-def-jam-co-founder-as-president-raises-us11m-for-global-push|title=Gushcloud names Def Jam co-founder as president, raises US$11m for global push|last=Tay|first=Vivienne|date=2019-09-18|website=The Business Times|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><ref name=\":4\"/>\n\n== Investments and acquisitions ==\nIn 2017, the company raised USD 3 million from South Korea\u2019s [[YGG (group)|YG Group]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.sg/gushcloud-raises-3-million-from-yg-investment-to-expand-its-influence-in-southeast-asia/|title=Gushcloud raises $3 million from YG Investment to expand its influence in Southeast Asia|last=Thomas|first=Sujin|date=2017-10-16|website=Business Insider Singapore|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asiaone.com/business/gushcloud-raises-4m-yg-investment-plans-expand-entertainment-groups-influence-sea|title=Gushcloud raises $4m from YG Investment, plans to expand entertainment group's influence in SEA|website=AsiaOne|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> a record label and media company, and an unspecified amount from Japan's D2C Inc, which is a joint venture between [[NTT Docomo]], [[Dentsu|Dentsu Inc]], and NTT Advertising, Inc.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.sg/singapores-gushcloud-to-open-japan-office-after-securing-investment-from-digital-advertising-company-d2c/|title=Singapore\u2019s Gushcloud to open Japan office after securing investment from digital advertising company D2C|last=Lin|first=Jessica|date=2017-11-10|website=Business Insider Singapore|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> In 2018, Gushcloud entered into a joint venture with YAN Digital, the digital arm of YAN Media Group<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-agency-enters-the-vietnam-market-via-jv/|title=Gushcloud Agency enters Vietnam via JV|date=2018-01-02|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> and Hahm Shout, a Korean public relations firm.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-bolsters-korean-ops-partnering-with-pr-firm-hahm-shout/|title=Gushcloud bolsters Korean ops partnering with PR firm Hahm Shout|last=Farveen|first=Farzanah|date=2018-08-07|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, the company invested in Summer Beauty House, a social commerce venture.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-eyes-beauty-space-partners-indonesia-based-beauty-community/|title=Gushcloud eyes beauty space, partners Indonesia-based beauty community|last=Tay|first=Vivienne|date=2018-05-07|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gadis.co.id/Try-It/summer-beauty-house-rumahnya-para-beauty-enthusiast|title=Summer Beauty House, Rumahnya Para Beauty Enthusiast|last=SkunkWorks|date=2018-05-15|website=gadis.co.id|language=id|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> In February 2019, Gushcloud International acquired the marketing agency, DSTNCT<ref name=\":0\" /> and launched Ribbit, a micro influencer network, in April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brandinginasia.com/instagram-influencer-asia-socialbakers/|title=Instagram influencer sponsored posts rose 189% in Asia: Socialbakers|date=2019-05-02|website=Branding in Asia Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-marketing-group-launches-micro-influencer-network-called-ribbit/|title=Gushcloud Marketing Group launches micro influencer network called Ribbit|last=Manjur|first=Rezwana|date=2019-04-25|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref> In February 2020, it acquired MODA Creative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asiatechdaily.com/gushcloud-moda-acquisition/|title=Gushcloud Acquires Australia\u2019s Digital Talent Startup MODA|date=2020-02-03|website=AsiaTechDaily - Asia's Leading Tech and Startup Media Platform|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>[https://ceoasiasummit.com/news/gushcloud-expands-its-footprint-in-australia-via-the-acquisition-of-moda-creatives/ Gushcloud expands its footprint in Australia via the acquisition of MODA Creatives]</ref> In September 2019, it raised USD 11 million from Korea Investment Partners, Golden Equator Capital, and Kejora Ventures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tnp.sg/news/business/spore-based-influencer-agency-gushcloud-international-raises-15m|title=S'pore-based influencer agency Gushcloud International raises $15m|date=2019-09-19|website=The New Paper|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asiaone.com/digital/gushcloud-raises-11-million-amid-growth-influencer-marketing|title=Gushcloud raises $11 million amid growth in influencer marketing|date=2019-09-19|website=AsiaOne|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://gushcloudinternational.com Official Website]\n\n[[Category:2011 establishments in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Talent agencies]]\n[[Category:Singaporean companies established in 2011]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Global influencer and talent acquisition company.}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Gushcloud International\n| logo = Gushcloud International Logo.png\n| type = Talent agency\n| industry = \n| fate = \n| predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = -->\n| successor = <!-- or: | successors = -->\n| founded = 2011, [[Singapore]]\n| founder = Althea Lim, Vincent Ha\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| hq_location_city = \n| hq_location_country = Singapore\n| area_served = Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines, Korea, Vietnam, Japan, China, and USA.\n| key_people = \n| products = \n| owner = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| num_employees = 300<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://cnaluxury.channelnewsasia.com/people/gushcloud-founders-althea-lim-vincent-ha-12064202|title=From crises to conquest: How Gushcloud's founders turned their business around|website=CNA Luxury|access-date=2019-11-13}}</ref>\n| num_employees_year = 2019<ref name=\":4\" />\n| parent = \n| website = https://gushcloud.com\n}}\n\n'''Gushcloud International''' is a global influencer, entertainment, and talent acquisition company. It is headquartered in [[Singapore]] and began in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-3m-yg-investment|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== History ==\nAlthea Lim and Vincent Ha are the co-founders of Gushcloud International,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-acquires-marketing-agency-dstnct/|title=Gushcloud acquires marketing agency DSTNCT|last=Farveen|first=Farzanah|date=2019-02-14|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> which has offices in Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand, Philippines, Vietnam, South Korea, Japan, and the US, and 300+ employees.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-splits-from-yello-digital-founders-buy-back-company-for-us8-2m/|title=Gushcloud splits from Yello Digital, founders buy back company for US$8.2m|last=Tan|first=Janice|date=2018-11-16|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.femina.co.id/Career/belajar-menjadi-influencer-sukses-di-media-sosial|title=Belajar Menjadi Influencer Sukses di Media Sosial|last=Indonesia|first=Femina|date=2018-04-22|website=femina.co.id|language=id|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> Gushcloud International works with influencers, content creators, and celebrities in Asia. The establishment has five working units: marketing, talent, investment, entertainment, and technology.<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nIn 2014, a blogger from Singapore, [[Xiaxue]], alleged that Gushcloud had unethical practices,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://says.com/my/news/everyone-is-talking-about-xiaxue-s-big-expose-on-gushcloud-can-i-have-a-summary-please|title=Everyone Is Talking About Xiaxue's Big Expos\u00e9 On Gushcloud. Can I Have A Summary Please?|last=Chu|first=Mei Mei|date=2014-12-24|website=SAYS|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> to which Gushcloud issued a point-by-point rebuttal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/singapore-startup-gushcloud-responds-xiaxues-accusations-lack-ethics|title=Singapore startup Gushcloud rebuts Xiaxue\u2019s accusations|last=Lee|first=Terence|date=23 December 2014|website=www.techinasia.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 2015, Xiaxue once again alleged that [[Singtel#Gushcloud marketing scandal|Gushcloud had paid celebrity bloggers]] to write negatively against the rivals of [[Singtel]], which Singtel and Gushcloud initially denied but later apologised.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-weathered-a-pr-disaster-its-now-growing-and-profitable|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mumbrella.asia/2015/03/gushcloud-exposed-for-paying-celebrity-bloggers-to-write-negatively-about-singtel-competitors-singtel-denies-issuing-brief|title=Xiaxue exposes Gushcloud for paying celebrity bloggers to write negatively about Singtel rivals, Singtel denies issuing brief|last=Hicks|first=Robin|date=2015-03-17|website=Mumbrella Asia|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tnp.sg/news/singtel-apologises-smear-campaign-against-rivals|title=Singtel apologises for smear campaign against rivals|last=Dhanaraj|first=Jennifer|date=2015-03-18|website=The New Paper|language=en|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Yello Digital Marketing Global (YDMG), based in [[South Korea]], gained control of the company by buying 62% shares for USD 7.5 million<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/gushcloud-weathered-a-pr-disaster-its-now-growing-and-profitable|title=Gushcloud weathered a PR disaster. It\u2019s now growing and profitable.|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/singapores-gushcloud-acquired-win-company|title=Tech in Asia - Connecting Asia's startup ecosystem|website=www.techinasia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> but in November 2018, the co-founders bought back the 62% shareholding from investor YDMG for USD 8.2 million.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-launches-new-sports-marketing-division/|title=Gushcloud launches new sports marketing division|date=2017-05-11|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> Between 2015 - 2018, it grew from three to nine markets.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nRussell Simmons, the co-founder of [[Def Jam Recordings]], became the President in September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/consumer/gushcloud-names-def-jam-co-founder-as-president-raises-us11m-for-global-push|title=Gushcloud names Def Jam co-founder as president, raises US$11m for global push|last=Tay|first=Vivienne|date=2019-09-18|website=The Business Times|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><ref name=\":4\"/>\n\n== Investments and acquisitions ==\nIn 2017, the company raised USD 3 million from South Korea\u2019s [[YGG (group)|YG Group]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.sg/gushcloud-raises-3-million-from-yg-investment-to-expand-its-influence-in-southeast-asia/|title=Gushcloud raises $3 million from YG Investment to expand its influence in Southeast Asia|last=Thomas|first=Sujin|date=2017-10-16|website=Business Insider Singapore|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asiaone.com/business/gushcloud-raises-4m-yg-investment-plans-expand-entertainment-groups-influence-sea|title=Gushcloud raises $4m from YG Investment, plans to expand entertainment group's influence in SEA|website=AsiaOne|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> a record label and media company, and an unspecified amount from Japan's D2C Inc, which is a joint venture between [[NTT Docomo]], [[Dentsu|Dentsu Inc]], and NTT Advertising, Inc.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.sg/singapores-gushcloud-to-open-japan-office-after-securing-investment-from-digital-advertising-company-d2c/|title=Singapore\u2019s Gushcloud to open Japan office after securing investment from digital advertising company D2C|last=Lin|first=Jessica|date=2017-11-10|website=Business Insider Singapore|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> In 2018, Gushcloud entered into a joint venture with YAN Digital, the digital arm of YAN Media Group<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-agency-enters-the-vietnam-market-via-jv/|title=Gushcloud Agency enters Vietnam via JV|date=2018-01-02|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> and Hahm Shout, a Korean public relations firm.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-bolsters-korean-ops-partnering-with-pr-firm-hahm-shout/|title=Gushcloud bolsters Korean ops partnering with PR firm Hahm Shout|last=Farveen|first=Farzanah|date=2018-08-07|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, the company invested in Summer Beauty House, a social commerce venture.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-eyes-beauty-space-partners-indonesia-based-beauty-community/|title=Gushcloud eyes beauty space, partners Indonesia-based beauty community|last=Tay|first=Vivienne|date=2018-05-07|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gadis.co.id/Try-It/summer-beauty-house-rumahnya-para-beauty-enthusiast|title=Summer Beauty House, Rumahnya Para Beauty Enthusiast|last=SkunkWorks|date=2018-05-15|website=gadis.co.id|language=id|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref> In February 2019, Gushcloud International acquired the marketing agency, DSTNCT<ref name=\":0\" /> and launched Ribbit, a micro influencer network, in April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brandinginasia.com/instagram-influencer-asia-socialbakers/|title=Instagram influencer sponsored posts rose 189% in Asia: Socialbakers|date=2019-05-02|website=Branding in Asia Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marketing-interactive.com/gushcloud-marketing-group-launches-micro-influencer-network-called-ribbit/|title=Gushcloud Marketing Group launches micro influencer network called Ribbit|last=Manjur|first=Rezwana|date=2019-04-25|website=Marketing Interactive|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-14}}</ref> In February 2020, it acquired MODA Creative.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asiatechdaily.com/gushcloud-moda-acquisition/|title=Gushcloud Acquires Australia\u2019s Digital Talent Startup MODA|date=2020-02-03|website=AsiaTechDaily - Asia's Leading Tech and Startup Media Platform|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>[https://ceoasiasummit.com/news/gushcloud-expands-its-footprint-in-australia-via-the-acquisition-of-moda-creatives/ Gushcloud expands its footprint in Australia via the acquisition of MODA Creatives]</ref> In September 2019, it raised USD 11 million from Korea Investment Partners, Golden Equator Capital, and Kejora Ventures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tnp.sg/news/business/spore-based-influencer-agency-gushcloud-international-raises-15m|title=S'pore-based influencer agency Gushcloud International raises $15m|date=2019-09-19|website=The New Paper|language=en|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><